# Optional: give each Govee H5075 sensor a friendly name.
#
# 1. Run `node demo.js` (in node/) to discover YOUR sensor names — they look
#    like GVH5075_XXXX, where XXXX is unique to each device.
# 2. Copy this file to ".env" in the project root:  cp .env.example .env
# 3. Map each device name to a name you choose.
#
# Format: <device_name>=<custom_name>   (blank lines and #comments are ignored)
# Any device not listed here is logged under its raw advertised name.
# .env is git-ignored, so your personal setup stays out of the repo.

# Example (replace with your own device names and labels):
GVH5075_XXXX=living-room
GVH5075_YYYY=garage
GVH5075_ZZZZ=bedroom
